# ThemeForest Restaurant Theme - Development Rules

You are building a premium ThemeForest-ready Restaurant Website Template.

## CRITICAL RULES - THEMEFOREST COMPLIANCE

### 1. ORIGINALITY (MANDATORY)
- Template MUST be original and not copied from other ThemeForest themes
- Do NOT replicate existing theme layouts 1:1
- Create unique section combinations and arrangements
- Use custom design patterns and component structures
- Reviewers WILL check for originality - failure results in rejection

### 2. LEGAL ASSETS ONLY (MANDATORY)
- **Images**: Use Unsplash/Pexels ONLY with proper attribution
  - Never embed copyrighted restaurant photos
  - Never use real restaurant branding/logos
  - Document all image sources in credits.md
- **Icons**: Lucide React (MIT licensed) ONLY
- **Fonts**: Google Fonts ONLY (Open Font License)
- **No paid assets**: Unless you have redistribution rights
- **Credits**: Maintain a comprehensive credits.md file

### 3. CODE QUALITY (MANDATORY)
- Clean, consistent naming conventions:
  - camelCase for variables and functions
  - PascalCase for React components
- NO unused imports or variables
- NO console.log statements in production code
- NO commented-out code blocks
- Proper comments for complex logic only
- Clean file structure and organization
- All imports organized and necessary

### 4. TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS

#### React Best Practices
- Use functional components with hooks
- Implement proper prop validation
- Use React.memo for performance where appropriate
- Implement error boundaries for production
- Follow React 18+ best practices

#### Tailwind CSS
- Use Tailwind utility classes consistently
- Implement design system through tailwind.config.js
- Use dark mode class strategy
- No inline styles unless absolutely necessary
- Responsive design: mobile-first approach
- Use @apply sparingly, prefer utility classes

#### Performance
- Lazy load images with loading="lazy"
- Code splitting with React.lazy for routes
- Optimize bundle size (target < 500KB initial)
- Remove unused Tailwind classes (purge enabled)
- Lighthouse score target: 90+ across all metrics

#### Accessibility
- Semantic HTML elements
- ARIA labels where needed
- Keyboard navigation support
- Focus states on interactive elements
- Alt text for all images
- Proper heading hierarchy

### 5. RESPONSIVE DESIGN
- Mobile-first approach mandatory
- Test at breakpoints: 320px, 640px, 768px, 1024px, 1280px, 1536px
- Touch-friendly interactions on mobile
- Proper text sizing and spacing
- No horizontal scroll on any device

### 6. DARK MODE
- Implement class-based dark mode
- All components must support dark variants
- Smooth transitions between themes
- Store preference in localStorage
- Test all pages in both modes

### 7. BROWSER COMPATIBILITY
- Support modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- No IE11 support required
- Use modern JavaScript (ES6+)
- CSS Grid and Flexbox are fine to use

### 8. SEO OPTIMIZATION
- Unique meta titles and descriptions per page
- Open Graph tags for social sharing
- Structured data (JSON-LD) for restaurant
- Semantic HTML throughout
- Proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3...)

### 9. DOCUMENTATION REQUIREMENTS
- Comprehensive installation guide
- Customization instructions (colors, fonts, images)
- Folder structure explanation
- How to add/remove pages
- Credits for all assets
- Browser support list
- Troubleshooting section

### 10. THEMEFOREST SUBMISSION CHECKLIST
- [ ] All pages functional and responsive
- [ ] Dark mode working everywhere
- [ ] Forms with proper validation
- [ ] No console errors
- [ ] No dead links
- [ ] Professional placeholder content
- [ ] Complete documentation
- [ ] Credits file with all sources
- [ ] Screenshots prepared (preview, pages, mobile, dark mode)
- [ ] Demo deployed and accessible
- [ ] Package structure correct

## DESIGN SYSTEM

### Colors (Modern Elegant Theme)
- Primary: Deep gold/amber (#D4AF37, amber-600)
- Secondary: Charcoal/slate (#334155, slate-700)
- Accent: Cream/beige (#F5F5DC, stone-200)
- Success: Emerald green
- Warning: Amber
- Error: Red
- Neutral: Gray scale

### Typography
- Headings: Playfair Display (Google Fonts)
- Body: Inter (Google Fonts)
- Sizes: Use Tailwind scale (text-sm, text-base, text-lg, etc.)

### Spacing
- Consistent padding/margin using Tailwind scale
- Section spacing: py-16 (mobile) to py-24 (desktop)
- Container: max-w-7xl with px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8

### Components Style
- Rounded corners: rounded-md (4px), rounded-lg (8px), rounded-xl (16px)
- Shadows: Elegant elevation (shadow-sm, shadow-md, shadow-lg)
- Transitions: duration-300, ease-in-out
- Hover states: subtle scale or color changes

## FOLDER STRUCTURE

src/
  assets/
    images/       # Placeholder images (Unsplash/Pexels)
    fonts/        # Google Fonts if needed
  components/
    ui/           # Button, Input, Card, Badge, Modal, etc.
    layout/       # Navbar, Footer, Layout
    sections/     # Hero, FeaturedDishes, Testimonials, etc.
  pages/          # All route pages
  routes/         # Router configuration
  data/           # Mock data (menu, testimonials, blog)
  hooks/          # Custom hooks (useTheme, useScrollSpy)
  contexts/       # Context providers (ThemeContext)
  styles/         # Global styles
  utils/          # Helper functions
docs/             # Documentation
public/           # Static assets

## DEVELOPMENT WORKFLOW

1. Build reusable UI components first
2. Create sections using UI components
3. Compose pages from sections
4. Implement features (dark mode, animations, forms)
5. Add SEO meta tags
6. Test responsiveness
7. Audit code quality
8. Create documentation
9. Package for ThemeForest

